org.apache.ignite.ml.math.impls.vector

Class SparseBlockDistributedVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.ml.math.impls.vector.AbstractVector
      • org.apache.ignite.ml.math.impls.vector.SparseBlockDistributedVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Externalizable, Serializable, Destroyable, MetaAttributes, StorageConstants, StorageOpsMetrics, Vector

    public class SparseBlockDistributedVector
extends AbstractVector
implements StorageConstants
    Sparse distributed vector implementation based on data grid.

    Unlike CacheVector that is based on existing cache, this implementation creates distributed cache internally and doesn't rely on pre-existing cache.

    You also need to call AbstractVector.destroy() to remove the underlying cache when you no longer need this vector.

    Currently fold supports only commutative operations.
